Self Introduction

My name is Sirisha Yamani. I am from India. At present, I am pursuing master's degree in Computer Science at Bridgewater State University and working as graduate assistant at College Of Education and Health Sciences Dean's Office. I have done my B.Tech in the field of Information Technology at VNR Vignana Jyothi Institute of Engineering and Technology Hyderabad, India. During the time of undergraduation, I have done internships at Virtusa Consulting Services and Capgemini Technology Services India Limited. Also, I have participated in Smart India Hackathon which is a nationwide hackathon and Microsoft WISE Program which is organized by Microsoft Corporation. After completing my undergraduation, I worked as Informatica Developer with the designation of Senior Analyst at Capgemini Technology Services India Limited. I have knowledge of C, C++, Java, Python, HTML, CSS, Javascript, Oracle, MS SQL Server, Informatica MDM - Customer 360, Informatica MDM - Product360, Informatica MDM Multidomain, OpenText Content Server , Linux and Windows operating systems.
